 121  2000              //  ______________________________________________________________________
 122  2000              //
 123  2000              //  Naming convention for Label vs Forth correspondance
 124  2000              //  Forth words are named as they are named for real with some exception to avoid assembler syntax errors.
 125  2000              //    - Leading "0" is converted into "Z_"
 126  2000              //    - Leading "(" is converted into "C_", closing bracket is omitted
 127  2000              //    - Leading numbers are converted in letters: ONE_  TWO_ etc.
 128  2000              //    - Question mark "?" is converted into "Q" or omitted if needed / useful.
 129  2000              //    - Plus sign "+" is converted in _PLUS or ADD_ depending.
 130  2000              //    - Minus sign "-" in L (for Line), MINUS or SUBTRACT depending
 131  2000              //    - Greater-Than sign ">" in _GREATER or TO_ depending
 132  2000              //    - Equal sign "=" is converted in EQUAL
 133  2000              //    - Less-Than sign "<" in _LESS or FROM_ (or TO_ again) depending
 134  2000              //    - Asterisk sign "*" is converted in _MUL or STAR
 135  2000              //    - Slash "/" is converted in _DIV or omitted if it is clear what it means
 136  2000              //    - Exclamation mark "!" is converted in STORE
 137  2000              //    - At-Sign "@" is converted in FETCH
 138  2000              //    - Words that collide with Assembler are normally suffixed with "_OP"
 139  2000
